---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead
      title="About — Marcos Augusto"
      description="A bit more about who I am and what I'm working on."
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <article class="prose">
        <h1>About</h1>

        <p class="lead">
          I'm Marcos Augusto, a software engineer based in Brazil. By day I work at
          <a href="https://nubank.com.br">Nubank</a>, mostly in Clojure, on systems that need to keep
          working for tens of millions of customers.
        </p>

        <p>
          By night and weekend I build small things — finance trackers, expense readers, sim-racing
          telemetry dashboards, home-control tools — and increasingly, agent infrastructure on top of
          <a href="https://opencode.ai">opencode</a> and Claude Code.
        </p>

        <p>
          Not all meaningful work fits into a public GitHub profile. Some projects stay private, like
          <code>fatura-reader</code>, <code>home-controle</code>, and my portfolio-tracking work, but
          I can still write about the problems, product decisions, and engineering tradeoffs without
          exposing the repositories. Other experiments, like <code>fechar-negocio</code>, are part of
          the same habit: turning a sharp personal or business itch into a working product surface.
        </p>

        <h2>What this blog is</h2>
        <p>
          A place to write down what I learn while doing the work. Not tutorials, not announcements —
          more like a public lab notebook.
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Agent skills, harnesses, orchestration.</strong> I use and curate a mixed set of
            agent workflows, some mine and some borrowed. I'll write about what holds up, what
            falls apart, and what is worth making your own.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Clojure in production.</strong> Patterns, anti-patterns, and the occasional war
            story from working on large systems.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Personal tools.</strong> The small fintech and tracker apps I build for myself —
            including some private repositories — and the design decisions behind them.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Sim racing.</strong> iRacing + SimHub dashboards, telemetry, and the weird
            native-code edges that come with it.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Stack I reach for</h2>
        <p>
          Clojure, TypeScript, Next.js, Flutter / Dart, Python, Postgres. Whatever the problem
          actually wants.
        </p>

        <h2>Get in touch</h2>
        <p>
          Easiest is <a href="https://x.com/maugusto___">X / Twitter</a> or
          <a href="mailto:augustoprofemp@gmail.com">email</a>. Code on
          <a href="https://github.com/maugustosemperfi">GitHub</a>.
        </p>
      </article>
    </main>
    <Footer />
    <style>
      .prose {
        max-width: 65ch;
        margin: 0 auto;
      }

      .prose h1 {
        margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
      }

      .prose h2 {
        margin-top: var(--space-12);
        margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
      }

      .prose p {
        margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
      }

      .prose ul {
        margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
      }

      .lead {
        font-size: var(--text-lg);
        line-height: var(--leading-snug);
        color: var(--color-text);
      }

      .lead a {
        font-weight: 500;
      }
    </style>
  </body>
</html>
